  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate whether patients with a preoperative reduced
      pulmonary function have a better preserved oxygenation capacity after open heart surgery,
      using either pulmonary perfusion or pulmoplegia compared with TAVI and the control-group with
      standard ECC (Extra Corporal Circulation).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
